				<div class="postbody">
				So, I started this new job and the IT department at this lab is actually competent and my web surfing is somewhat on the more restrictive side.  Not that I should be surfing the net for non-business reasons to begin with, but I took an entry level, lower than dirt job due to my lame butt being unemployed for ~five months and entry level is better than nothing.  However I get my stuff done mega quick like and I get real freaking bored.
<br />

<br />
So, I am not too sure exactly how this proxy server stuff works and I am really just more curious about how things work rather than actually wanting to do things I shouldn't.
<br />

<br />
My question is:  can one set up a home PC to act as a proxy server whereby you surf on over via the internet to your home PC while on the work PC then you surf the net thru your home PC so you can access off limit sites?
<br />

<br />
Are there any proxy server type websites that you can go to then be able to surf to other websites thru a proxy site?
<br />

<br />
I want to get in good with the company I am at, so I don't plan on intentionally causing issues but my curiousity was perked up.  At work I even Googled up "proxy servers" to see what I could learn but all websites dealing with proxy servers seem to be banned; guess I was not the first person to be thinking what I was thinking.<br />
